The paper deals with a problem in data science and machine learning related to linear regression on dynamic graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also proposes randomized algorithms that utilize subsampled randomized Hadamard transform and CountSketch, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and signal processing. Hence, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with optimization and approximation algorithms, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
